      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINER MICK (8) is a consistent type who is having his first try here. Raced on speed and lifted strongly to score a 4.5 lengths win over 460m at Geelong (25.53). Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Expected to go well again. VICTORY YACHT (2) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (28.31) at this track behind Whisky Bella in a Grade 5. Stalked the pace but found the line strongly. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Will give a great sight again. ZIPPING SWEENY (1) is progressing well and looks close to another win after hitting the frame from Box 7 last run (25.07) at Sale. Boasts a strong record from this draw with three wins and two minor placings from seven starts. Can feature again. KRAKEN TOMMY (3) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
